                     <interp inst="t18281204-259-person2229" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . Webster, who took the prisoner, gave me the duplicates; she said Mrs. Davis gave her leave to pawn them.</p>
               <p>MRS. DAVIS. I never gave her leave to pawn them; the duplicates were left in the lodgings.</p>
               <p>The prisoner put in a written defence, stating that the prosecutrix had authorised him to pledge the goods.</p>
